 medieval Islam Organised around the lives and works of 6 Muslim men, each highlighting a different aspect of bodily differenceAddresses broad cultural questions relating to social class, religious orthodoxy, moral reputation, drug use, male homoeroticism and self-representation in the public sphereMoves towards a coherent theory of medieval disability and bodily aesthetics in Islamic cultural traditions  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aIslamic Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074864507740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748645084zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748645084zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748645084/original  a978-3-11-078046-8 Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA